Option 5 – Continuous Development with Late Release Branch Creation
Overview
Here, the “develop” branch that will act as integration branch for developers and “release” branch will 
act as testing branch for SIT team.
● In this model, feature development occurs independently through dedicated feature branches.
● Feature branches continue to merge back into “develop” branch for developer testing.
● Features which are developed and ready, can be merged to “release” branch and marked as 
ready for SIT testing.
● SIT team can test one/any/all features and test it sequentially or parallel and mark features as 
SIT approved and keep it in “release” branch only.
A Release Branch is created only after the Bank approves the final feature scope.
Key Principles
● Once the bank asks for feature UAT testing, a versioned release will be created.
● This versioned release can be deployed to SIT / UAT
● One round of SIT testing this branch will be handed to UAT team.
● The same branch once approved by UAT will be given to ISD team.
● Once the production date is fixed, the same UAT/ISD approved branch will be deployed on 
Preprod.
● Preprod approved release branch to be deployed on prod and merged back to main
● Main will be synced to develop, release.
Example
 Feature Development From develop Branch
○ Feature B = In Dev
 All Features merged to develop Branch, develop Branch contains:
○ Feature A = Dev Done
○ Feature B = In Dev
○ Feature C = Dev Done
○ Feature D = Dev Done
 SIT:
○ Feature A = SIT Approved
○ Feature C = SIT In Progress
○ Feature D = SIT Approved
 UAT:
○ Feature A = UAT Approved
○ Feature D = UAT In Progress
