Pros
● Bank fully controls release content.
● No feature flags are required.
● There is no need to change the current deployment model.
● No need for extra environment, existing environments (develop, sit, uat) can be used.
● Better governance and auditability.
● All developed features can be deployed to SIT for SIT testing
● SIT can test parallel multiple features.
● With no long-lived feature branches, all developed code sits into common develop branch.
● Single source of truth code branch for each stage, for developer “develop” branch and for SIT 
testing “release” branch.
● No Surprise deployment by other leads as only develop and release base code will be deployed 
on develop / SIT environments.
● Supports changing business priorities.
Cons
● Longer release cycle.
● Cherry Picking Required
● Higher testing effort.
● Release branch created late in lifecycle.
